summary: CRV WAS IN PARK, TURNED ON IGNITION, CLOSED DRIVER DOOR AND WENT AROUND TO BACK DOOR TO GET SOMETHING FROM THE BACK SEAT; CAR LOCKS LOCKED WHEN I CLOSED DOOR. WE HAD TO JIMMY THE CAR LOCK OPEN WHILE CAR WAS ON.   NOW, ONE OF THE BACK LOCKS SOUNDS LIKE A MACHINE GUN WHEN WE LOCK THE CAR WITH THE FOB OR WHEN THE LOCKS CLOSE  THEMSELVES AFTER REACHING A CERTAIN SPEED.
